, you had to restart Claude Code every time you modified skills\n- Now skill changes take effect immediately without restarting\n- Major efficiency improvement for workflow development\n\n**2. 80+ New Features Including:**\n- 30+ new features\n- 40+ bug fixes\n- 10+ performance optimizations\n\n**3. Other Notable Improvements:**\n- Enhanced Vim operations\n- Terminal compatibility improvements\n- Multi-language response configuration\n- MCP (Model Context Protocol) dynamic updates\n- Better CLI interactions\n- Improved prompt behavior for more accurate code generation\n\n### How to Update:\n```bash\nnpm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n# or\nnpm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.1\n```\n\n### Check Version:\n```bash\nclaude --version\n```\n\n**Note:** The search results don't show any February 2026 updates yet. The most recent information is from the January 2026 update. If there are newer features released in February, they may not have been widely documented or indexed yet. I recommend checking the [official GitHub repository](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code) for the most up-to-date changelog.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
