 and modify code in repositories\n- **Integration with VS Code**: Copilot features being integrated into VS Code core\n\n#### **Platform Expansions:**\n- Support for more IDEs: Neovim, JetBrains (IntelliJ, PyCharm)\n- Multi-line code completion for Java, C, C++, C#\n- Windows Terminal integration (free tier: 50 chat requests/month)\n- Xcode support in preview\n\n### 🔮 **Upcoming/Latest Features**\n- GPT-5 integration (announced August 2025)\n- Claude Opus 4.5 integration (announced November 2025)\n- Copilot Free tier available\n\n---\n\n**For the most current and official information**, I recommend checking:\n- [GitHub Blog](https://github.blog)\n- [GitHub Copilot Documentation](https://docs.github.com/copilot)\n- [GitHub Changelog](https://github.blog/changelog/)\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about any particular feature or timeframe?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
