uary 2026) - Integrating directly into the IDE ecosystem\n- **Key capabilities:**\n  - **1 million token context window** - Massive context for understanding entire codebases\n  - **CLAUDE.md project memory** - Persistent project context across sessions\n  - **Sub-agents** - Specialized AI assistants for code review, frontend development, backend architecture\n  - **Plan Mode** - Creates detailed implementation plans before coding\n  - **MCP protocol extensions** - Connects to databases, APIs, browsers\n  - **Agent Skills** - Now an open standard shared across tools\n  - **Hooks automation** - Auto-executes formatting, testing, and code checks around file edits\n\n**Performance:** Users report 40% average productivity improvement; features that took weeks now completed in days\n\n---\n\n## **Cursor**\n\n**Major Updates:**\n- **Version 2.4 (2026)** - New Multi-agent Judging and Plan Mode features\n- **New Features:**\n  - **Multi-agent Judging** - Automatic code review functionality\n  - **Plan Mode** - Development planning with automatic Mermaid flowchart generation\n  - **Multi-Agent parallel processing** - Up to 8 agents working simultaneously (2026 addition)\n  - **Background Agent** - Executes code modifications, terminal commands, and dependency installation without real-time monitoring\n  - **Yolo mode** - More intelligent command execution with parallel task processing\n  \n**Technical Enhancements:**\n- Built-in **Composer model** for faster generation (4x speed improvement in version 2.0)\n- Supports **local model deployment** for privacy and speed\n- **Code traceability and AI generation marking** for team collaboration\n- Git worktree isolation for parallel agent work\n\n**Pricing:** Pro plan at $16/month (60% more expensive than GitHub Copilot), with \"unlimited use\" mode announced in June 2025\n\n---\n\n## **GitHub Copilot**\n\n**Key Features in 2026:**\n- **Copilot Workspace** - Full automation from Issue to PR\n- **Copilot CLI** - Autopilot mode, $10/month Pro pricing\n- **VS Code integration** - Enhanced inline suggestions (up to 3 suggestions)\n- **Advanced configuration options** - Enable/disable for specific file types\n\n---\n\n## **Industry Trends (February 2026)**\n\n1. **Evolution from \"Code Completion\" to \"Autonomous Agents\"**\n   - All three platforms now support multi-agent workflows\n   - Developer role shifting from \"writing code\" to \"orchestrating AI agents\"\n\n2. **Main Themes for 2026:**\n   - **Background Agents war** - Competition in autonomous task execution\n   - **MCP standardization** - Cross-tool protocol compatibility\n   - **Multi-model approaches** - Supporting multiple AI models per platform\n\n3. **Performance benchmarks:**\n   - Cursor: Most interactions completed within 30 seconds\n   - Claude Code: 40% average productivity improvement reported\n   - All tools: Massive context windows (100K-1M tokens)\n\n---\n\n## **Quick Setup Commands (February 2026)**\n\n**Claude Code:**\n```bash\nnpm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\ncd your-project && claude\nclaude \"Replace all console.log with structured logging\"\n```\n\n**Cursor (.cursorrules):**\n```typescript\nYou are an expert in TypeScript, React, and Node.js.\n- Use functional components with hooks\n- Prefer named exports over default exports\n- Write concise comments in Chinese for complex logic\n```\n\n**VS Code (Copilot config):**\n```json\n{\n  \"github.copilot.enable\": {\"*\": true, \"markdown\": true},\n  \"github.copilot.advanced\": {\"inlineSuggestCount\": 3},\n  \"editor.inlineSuggest.enabled\": true\n}\n```\n\nThe search results indicate intense competition in February 2026, with all three tools rapidly evolving toward autonomous multi-agent systems that can handle complex development tasks with minimal human intervention.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
