 about benchmark claims\n\n---\n\n## **Gemini 3.1 Pro** (Released February 20, 2026)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- ARC-AGI-2 score of 77.1% (doubled from Gemini 3 Pro's 31.1%)\n- Won 12 out of 16 benchmark tests against competitors\n- Support for 1 million token context\n- Enhanced reasoning capabilities\n- **Free for all users** (Pro and Ultra users get higher quotas)\n- Available in Gemini App, AI Studio, NotebookLM, Vertex AI, and other Google tools\n\n**Performance Notes:**\n- Surpassed Claude Opus 4.6, Claude Sonnet 4.6, and GPT-5.2 in multiple tests\n- GPQA Diamond: 94.3%\n- SWE-Bench Verified: 80.6%\n- However, Claude still performed better in some practical tasks like GDPval-AA (office tasks)\n\n---\n\n## **GPT-5.3** (Expected February 2026)\n\n**Information Found:**\n- GPT-5.3 Codex was reportedly released **20 minutes after** Claude Opus 4.6 on February 5, 2026\n- Designed specifically for programming tasks to compete with Claude\n- Terminal-Bench 2.0 score of 77.3% (mentioned in some reports)\n- Limited official information available; mostly discussed through leaks and rumors\n- Some sources mention it being in small-scale testing\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nWhile I couldn't locate the specific Hacker News discussions you mentioned, the search results show these were major releases in February 2026 that generated significant discussion across developer communities. If you're looking for the actual Hacker News comment threads, you might want to:\n\n1. Search directly on [Hacker News](https://news.ycombinator.com/) for these topics\n2. Check if the discussion threads might have different titles or search terms\n3. Verify the exact dates of the discussions\n\nWould you like me to try a different search approach or look for additional information about any specific aspect of these models?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
